==Finnish==
([[Wiktionary:Finnish index t|index T]])

===Adjective===
'''tumma''' (tummempi, tummin)

# [[dark]] [[colour]]
#:''Hänellä on tumma tukka. (She has dark hair.)''

====Usage notes====
As an adjective, ''tumma'' normally describes the subject to be dark of color. If a person is the subject, it often just means that they have dark hair and/or eyes, and not necessarily that their skin color was dark. Also it doesn't necessarily mean that the peson in question was a gypsy.

#:''Naapurin jätkä seurustelee taas sen tumman tytön kanssa.'' the guy next door dates the dark-haired/eyed girl again.

====Antonyms====
*[[vaalea]]

===Noun===
'''tumma''' (plural ''tummat'')
# (person) [[mustalainen]] ([[gypsy]] or [[rom]])

====Usage notes====
As a reference to any number greater than one of gypsies, the word is used in the plural case ''tummat''. The singular case is seldom used alone in reference to one gypsy. 

#:''Naapurin jätkän tyttökaveri vaikuttaa olevan tumma.'' The next door guy's girlfriend appears to be a gypsy.
#:''Tummat kruisasivat Mersullaan kylän halki.'' The gypsies cruised through the town in their Mercedes Benz.

